{"comments":"TypeContrast - typographic contrast levels and accessibility variants.\n\n\"Contrast\" in typography refers to:\n1. **Stroke contrast**: Variation between thick and thin strokes in letterforms\n2. **Size contrast**: Ratio between heading and body sizes\n3. **Weight contrast**: Difference between light and bold weights\n4. **Color contrast**: Luminance ratio for accessibility (WCAG)\n\nThis module focuses on accessibility contrast and readability adaptations\nfor different visual contexts and user needs.\n\n## Contrast levels\n\n- **High**: Maximum differentiation (accessibility mode)\n- **Normal**: Standard contrast (default)\n- **Reduced**: Softer contrast (reduced eye strain)\n\n## Use cases\n\n- **High contrast**: Vision impairment, bright ambient light, aging users\n- **Reduced contrast**: Dark mode refinement, extended reading, luxury aesthetics\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[73,14],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeContrast.purs","start":[73,3]},"title":"LevelHigh"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[74,16],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeContrast.purs","start":[74,3]},"title":"LevelNormal"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[75,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeContrast.purs","start":[75,3]},"title":"LevelReduced"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Typography","TypeContrast"],"ContrastLevel"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[77,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Typography/TypeContrast.purs","start":[77,1]},"title":"eqContrastLevel"},{"co